1
00:00:30,460 --> 00:00:32,790
Do you have any liquor?

2
00:00:35,580 --> 00:00:38,450
Why have you come here looking for a drink?

3
00:00:38,450 --> 00:00:41,610
Give me  a shot of whatever you have.

4
00:00:41,610 --> 00:00:45,430
Recently I've gotten mixed up in a lot of really weird stuff.

5
00:00:49,690 --> 00:00:51,850
What kind of things?

6
00:00:54,070 --> 00:00:56,680
You know what Yun Yeong Gil told you?

7
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:59,680
"It's not just people who see things", etc.

8
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:02,060
I felt leery about that, so I did a little digging of his past.

9
00:01:02,060 --> 00:01:05,640
And went to the café he frequented.

10
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:10,470
That's where I ran into Hong Yi Yeong.

11
00:01:11,710 --> 00:01:14,770
Hong Yi Yeong went to such a place?

12
00:01:14,770 --> 00:01:20,420
Yes, she has no fear. Yesterday and today, twice, I met her there.

13
00:01:20,420 --> 00:01:24,370
Today, it seemed like she received a CD from the owner.

14
00:01:24,370 --> 00:01:29,050
Because I was curious, I called her to come talk to me.

15
00:01:29,050 --> 00:01:32,540
- The instant she spotted me, she ran away.
- So then?

16
00:01:32,540 --> 00:01:37,850
I followed her to find out why she ran away, and worst luck, she got into an accident.

17
00:01:38,590 --> 00:01:42,020
- There was an accident?
- Telling you about it is complicated.

18
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:45,900
In any case, she got hurt.  She was hit by a car.

19
00:01:46,890 --> 00:01:50,750
Yi Yeong got hit by a car?  Where is she right now?

20
00:01:50,750 --> 00:01:52,440
Where else, she would be at a hospital.

21
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:56,620
You didn't  see her off to a hospital and came here instead?

22
00:01:56,620 --> 00:01:59,520
Why are you yelling at me? I didn't do it.

23
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:03,780
A high school kid suddenly ran out into the street and that's what happened!

24
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:26,360
Why are you here?

25
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,990
I heard from Professor Kang. I came to see her for a second.

26
00:02:28,990 --> 00:02:32,830
What did he tell you? Didn't he tell you it was because of him?

27
00:02:32,830 --> 00:02:35,360
Did you come here with any sense of shame?  Are you in your right mind now?

28
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:39,530
I only want to know her condition. You're here too for the same reason.

29
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,630
Director, how did you ...

30
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:19,400
I'm sorry.  It's very late. I heard about the accident.

31
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,970
Yes.

32
00:03:21,970 --> 00:03:25,620
As late it is ...

33
00:03:26,510 --> 00:03:31,170
she still hasn't regained consciousness.

34
00:03:36,660 --> 00:03:38,550
I am sorry.

35
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:43,760
Why should you be? Someone else did this.

36
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:59,090
Let's go out and talk.

37
00:04:17,790 --> 00:04:22,000
- How does it feel, seeing her injured?
- Ask what you truly want to ask.

38
00:04:24,790 --> 00:04:30,170
Someone sent me a video showing you killing Yun Yeong Gil.

39
00:04:31,830 --> 00:04:33,740
Would you like to see it?

40
00:04:52,590 --> 00:04:54,840
You finally found it. Congratulations.

41
00:04:54,840 --> 00:05:00,480
You lied to me and that's all you have to say now?

42
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,630
You killed him because he knows what you did a year ago, didn't you?

43
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:04,850
I only pushed him because we were fighting. You know that if you watched the video.

44
00:05:04,850 --> 00:05:06,970
- You could have grabbed him.
- I couldn't.

45
00:05:06,970 --> 00:05:10,490
- Why didn't you call the hospital immediately?
- There was the concert.  Everyone was waiting.

46
00:05:10,490 --> 00:05:14,880
- Is that your excuse?
- I'm just telling you the truth.

47
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:19,730
I'm sorry, but everything you think is not correct.

48
00:05:19,730 --> 00:05:22,380
Then can you give me an answer?

49
00:05:23,180 --> 00:05:26,110
Who exactly killed my brother?

50
00:05:28,290 --> 00:05:33,470
The night of the accident,  Hong Yi Yeong, Ian, Yun Yeong Gil, and  you were at the scene of the accident.

51
00:05:33,470 --> 00:05:36,260
Two of them are dead.

52
00:05:36,260 --> 00:05:39,170
Yun Yeong Gil is one of the witnessess who saw Ian die.

53
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:45,100
This video shows the scene of  you killing the witness.

54
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:48,970
I can't think of anything other than that you killed Ian.

55
00:05:48,970 --> 00:05:53,510
Everything points to you.  Why do you continue to deny it?

56
00:05:54,540 --> 00:06:00,260
The reason for killing Yun Yeong Gil is because he saw you kill Ian.  Isn't that it?

57
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:04,260
No. I didn't intend to kill him.

58
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:07,190
You killed him anyway.

59
00:06:10,110 --> 00:06:12,460
Turn yourself in.  I'll give you the opportunity.

60
00:06:12,460 --> 00:06:16,310
And tell me.  Tell me who killed Ian.

61
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:19,000
How can I tell you something I don't know?

62
00:06:19,860 --> 00:06:24,780
Director, do you know what is the thing that is driving the most crazy?

63
00:06:25,550 --> 00:06:29,520
For a while I thought Hong Yi Yeong was the murderer and I hurt and tormented her.

64
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,690
And you just saw her now, didn't you?

65
00:06:31,690 --> 00:06:34,800
Don't you feel anything when an innocent person gets injured and is lying there like that?

66
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:38,920
You know everything about that day, don't you? Why exactly won't you tell me everything?

67
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:44,110
If you keep your mouth shut, there could be another victim.

68
00:06:44,110 --> 00:06:50,100
Do you want to see someone else get hurt and die? Is it Hong Yi Yeong's turn next?

69
00:06:51,590 --> 00:06:54,780
- Just exactly who killed Ian?
- I don't know either.

70
00:06:54,780 --> 00:06:55,980
Tell me.

71
00:06:55,980 --> 00:06:59,490
I don't know either. How many times have I've told you?  I said I don't know.

72
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:03,900
It's just that you won't believe me.

73
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:21,130
I Wanna Hear Your Song

74
00:08:21,970 --> 00:08:24,790
SY Arts Center

75
00:08:25,930 --> 00:08:29,660
How serious is it?  Did she get hurt badly?

76
00:08:30,550 --> 00:08:33,560
Yes, I understand. I will pay a visit.

77
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:41,450
Starting with taking the facility rents from  the corporate funds,

78
00:08:41,450 --> 00:08:45,910
inflated expenses through false expenditure resolutions,

79
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:48,660
but the details of the chairwoman's use of the corporate credit card are spectacular.

80
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:51,540
So how many years will you serve if this is given to the prosecutor?

81
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:54,850
Are you alright with being the scapegoat?

82
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:05,680
Welcome to the Jungle: Anonymous Bulletin Board
Yu Da:  Nam Ju Wan is a murderer.

83
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:09,190
Yu Da: I saw it that night. Yun Yeong Gil was killed.

84
00:09:09,190 --> 00:09:11,950
He was pushed down the stairs.

85
00:09:16,830 --> 00:09:19,260
- Assistant Yang.
- Yes?

86
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:22,130
Please assist the conductor for a while.

87
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:23,700
What about Hong Yi Yeong?

88
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,660
She must have had an accident. She's injured.

89
00:09:25,660 --> 00:09:28,030
She won't be able to come to work for a while.

90
00:09:44,890 --> 00:09:48,320
- Did you get a call about Hong Yi Yeong?
- Yeah.

91
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:52,480
Until Yi Yeong returns to work, Assistant Yang will assist you.

92
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:58,210
Did you see the chat group bulletin board?

93
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:01,450
I did.

94
00:10:01,450 --> 00:10:04,000
Don't pay attention to that kind of message.

95
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,410
I don't think you should leave Yu Da alone.

96
00:10:06,410 --> 00:10:09,800
I'll use this opportunity to ask the police to investigate.

97
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:14,180
But you won't ask me if it's true or not?

98
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:16,800
Ninety out of a hundred posts on the message board are trash.

99
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:20,280
If you get worked up over every single one, you can't survive.

100
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:23,930
What do you want to do? I'm sure the members will agree.

101
00:10:23,930 --> 00:10:28,060
If it's hard for you to rehearse today, I'll tell them the rehearsal is canceled.

102
00:10:29,450 --> 00:10:31,610
Never mind.

103
00:10:32,370 --> 00:10:35,880
I'll do it. Please tell them to come to the rehearsal.

104
00:10:37,090 --> 00:10:39,680
Hello, Professor.

105
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:44,020
- Oh,  wait a sec,  you two are preparing for the competition, right?
- Yes.

106
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:45,960
- Professor Kim's lessons are good?
- Yes.

107
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:49,870
Study well. Her husband is one of the judges. Work hard.

108
00:10:49,870 --> 00:10:52,960
- Thank you.
- Bye.

109
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,540
What the... ? Hey!

110
00:10:54,540 --> 00:10:56,490
Bastard, won't you let go? Let go.

111
00:10:56,490 --> 00:10:59,990
Won't you let me go? Hey, this is an assault.

112
00:10:59,990 --> 00:11:03,340
I warned you, didn't I? I said to sit quietly at home.

113
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:05,690
Hey, are you being like this because of Hong Yi Yeong?

114
00:11:05,690 --> 00:11:09,530
Why are you taking it out of me because she got hurt?

115
00:11:09,530 --> 00:11:13,070
Curse the middle school student who ran into the street. Are you listening?

116
00:11:13,070 --> 00:11:16,980
I know you and Nam Ju Wan are on the same team.

117
00:11:16,980 --> 00:11:21,600
You control this school.  I also know  this school and Sinyeong Philharmonic are one body.

118
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:24,210
You just wait. I will reveal everything, got it?

119
00:11:24,210 --> 00:11:26,960
This bastard... oh!

120
00:11:28,660 --> 00:11:32,670
This child who doesn't know anything about how the world words.

121
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:35,260
What will you reveal? Who will allow it?

122
00:11:35,260 --> 00:11:41,750
Looks like you're trusting in your father and running amok, but if you ever come near me again,

123
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:44,570
I will report you.

124
00:11:46,740 --> 00:11:48,760
Remember that, bastard.

125
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:01,330
- Has Hong Yi Yeong woken up?
- No, not yet.

126
00:12:01,330 --> 00:12:03,190
What did Father say?

127
00:12:03,190 --> 00:12:05,920
He plans on turning everything over to the prosecutor's office.

128
00:12:07,290 --> 00:12:11,680
You need to hang tight.  He is someone who will create a loophole.

129
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:15,260
Right. What do you want to do about Manager Yun?

130
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:18,250
She'll figure it out on her own.

131
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:24,280
Your face is a mess. Go home and get some sleep. I'll stop by the hospital.

132
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:27,950
- Alright.
- I'm going.

133
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:39,980
Maestro Nam, I think we shouldn't rehearse today.

134
00:12:39,980 --> 00:12:42,470
Why, is there a problem?

135
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:46,490
The thing is ... today they are boycotting the rehearsal.

136
00:12:46,490 --> 00:12:50,810
The principal oboist and the members are discussing.

137
00:12:51,530 --> 00:12:52,890
Where?

138
00:12:52,890 --> 00:12:58,570
What has happened that you would gather like this? You are all being too much.

139
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:04,750
This morning's post is eye-opening, but things are noisy  because of the murder case.

140
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:10,590
Don't gossip behind each other's backs, and share information openly. That's why I called this meeting.

141
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:17,310
What is there to talk about between us? Shouldn't we ask the conductor himself?

142
00:13:17,310 --> 00:13:19,250
To see if he's the real murderer or not.

143
00:13:19,890 --> 00:13:24,950
Hey. Why don't you ask him? If he really killed someone or not.

144
00:13:27,030 --> 00:13:31,010
Anyway, isn't it too much to boycott rehearsals like this?

145
00:13:31,010 --> 00:13:34,620
It's just a post on the bulletin board, after all.

146
00:13:40,370 --> 00:13:44,690
What are you all doing here? Aren't you coming to rehearsal?

147
00:13:44,690 --> 00:13:51,060
I'm sorry. The atmosphere had been gloomy lately, so I thought we'd have a discussion.

148
00:13:54,250 --> 00:14:00,360
Conductor! Is today's post on the bulletin board true?

149
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:04,800
- Did you really kill someone?
- Seriously...

150
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:12,160
I won't dignify that with a response. Rehearsal starts in 15 minutes.

151
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:14,200
If you don't want to come, you don't have to.

152
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:22,480
But if anyone doesn't show up for a reason I find unacceptable, then  I'll have no choice but to exercise my prerogatives.

153
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:51,210
You said you were afraid, so why did you post the message on the bulletin board?

154
00:14:52,610 --> 00:14:59,800
I thought about it, and I don't know if the dead person was good or bad,

155
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:04,520
but someone died, nonetheless. And I saw him die.

156
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:08,280
It's going to reach the police ears.  I'm sure there will be an investigation.

157
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:09,700
Then what should I do?

158
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:14,090
You have a lot on your phone, right? Footage you recorded illegally.

159
00:15:14,090 --> 00:15:17,120
Get rid of it quickly.

160
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:24,070
Conductor's Room

161
00:15:32,650 --> 00:15:35,050
What's the occasion?

162
00:15:40,510 --> 00:15:45,730
I heard you had rehearsal. I wonder what the atmosphere was like. You're quite amazing.

163
00:15:45,730 --> 00:15:48,200
Did you come to taunt me?

164
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,600
When are you going to go to the police?

165
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:53,950
If you don't,  they'll find you first. That will make it worse for you.

166
00:15:53,950 --> 00:15:56,460
Isn't that what you want?

167
00:15:56,460 --> 00:15:59,810
You even have the evidence, why don't you report me?

168
00:16:00,590 --> 00:16:06,150
If you are caught like that, you will shut your mouth about last year's incident. I won't be able to make you reveal the other crimes.

169
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:10,970
Once I learn everything I need to know, I'll send you there myself.

170
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:15,930
So what if you get to know who killed Ian? There's no evidence and the witness is dead.

171
00:16:15,930 --> 00:16:18,880
I'll wonder about that after I find the culprit.

172
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:23,090
Could you say that so easily if your own sibling died, huh?

173
00:16:24,090 --> 00:16:27,890
What I want to know is extremely simple.

174
00:16:27,890 --> 00:16:31,320
Who killed Ian that day.

175
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:37,570
This is your last chance. If you don't tell me right now, I'll reveal all the videos I have.

176
00:16:37,570 --> 00:16:43,120
Then you will become the murderer of both Yun Yeong Gil and Kim Ian. Is that okay?

177
00:16:43,950 --> 00:16:47,270
I'll tell you this again. I did not kill Kim Ian.

178
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:51,010
It's not that I'm not telling you, I have nothing to tell you. You're choosing not to believe me.

179
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:54,540
You have no evidence, and I didn't even see Ian die.

180
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:12,110
Yi Yeong. Yi Yeong, are you awake?

181
00:17:13,210 --> 00:17:16,500
Unni?

182
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:19,610
Thank goodness. If you woke up, that's enough.

183
00:17:19,610 --> 00:17:23,360
Everyone was worried because you should've woken up a while ago.

184
00:17:34,580 --> 00:17:39,330
- What about the kid?
- The one you pushed? Not a single scratch.

185
00:17:39,330 --> 00:17:44,060
Her family even came by earlier to thank you.

186
00:17:46,130 --> 00:17:48,780
That's a relief.

187
00:17:48,780 --> 00:17:50,580
What about Aunt?

188
00:17:50,580 --> 00:17:55,590
She stayed all night and finally left. She'll bring some clothes.

189
00:17:58,690 --> 00:18:01,610
They're calling for me. I'll be back.

190
00:18:01,610 --> 00:18:05,710
Don't worry about anything and just rest, okay?

191
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:58,110
There's no evidence? You want me to believe that?

192
00:18:58,110 --> 00:19:01,840
You took Yun Yeong Gil's bag. That's evidence.

193
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:05,300
Why'd you take it? What the heck is in it?

194
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:10,100
This is footage from yesterday, from 6:12 P.M. to 6:15 P.M.

195
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:15,630
What's in there isn't the evidence you want. It's all meaningless stuff.

196
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:19,990
Meaningless stuff, such as?  A ballpoint pen?  It's Professor Kang's, correct?

197
00:19:19,990 --> 00:19:25,710
That's why Ian died, Yi Yeong lost her memory, and you killed Yun Yeong Gil.

198
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:30,060
What the hell is inside the pen?

199
00:19:32,090 --> 00:19:37,910
All the money Professor Kang embezzled from the school. From big to small, everything.

200
00:19:38,390 --> 00:19:41,110
- Which of them did you participate in?
- I didn't participate.  I'm a victim too.

201
00:19:41,110 --> 00:19:44,910
You killed someone, don't play the victim.

202
00:19:47,330 --> 00:19:50,410
I received support in my musical career.

203
00:19:50,410 --> 00:19:53,150
He's been helping me for a long time, even until now.

204
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:58,600
I finished my studies thanks to him, and even joined the Asia Philharmonic.

205
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:05,670
Alright, let's say you didn't kill Ian.

206
00:20:05,670 --> 00:20:10,000
In the end, you just kept quiet about his death because of that money?

207
00:20:10,850 --> 00:20:14,780
You shut your eyes to Ian's death and in return were appointed to a permanent position?

208
00:20:14,780 --> 00:20:16,500
Right?

209
00:20:19,430 --> 00:20:21,290
Yeah.

210
00:20:22,540 --> 00:20:24,900
Do you have any other questions?

211
00:20:27,580 --> 00:20:32,200
Was it a coincidence that Professor Kang showed up twice at the café which Yun Yeong Gil frequented?

212
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:34,890
Tell me everything you know.

213
00:20:43,010 --> 00:20:45,530
Professor Kang is searching for something.

214
00:20:45,530 --> 00:20:50,340
Even if he pretends not to care, inwardly he's very anxious because of that.

215
00:20:51,150 --> 00:20:53,870
What is that?

216
00:20:53,870 --> 00:20:57,690
I don't know. Yun Yeong Gill accidentally let it slip out.

217
00:20:57,690 --> 00:21:01,330
In the absence of a detailed explanation, it might have been a lie.

218
00:21:01,330 --> 00:21:02,640
What did he let slip?

219
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:06,660
He said, "Do you think there are no witnesses on the day Kim Ian died?"

220
00:21:06,660 --> 00:21:09,120
"It's not just people who see things."

221
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:10,800
What did he mean by that?

222
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:15,620
Does it mean that Yun Yeong Gil had some sort of evidence?

223
00:21:15,620 --> 00:21:17,400
Who would know?

224
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:20,950
It could be a lie or there could be a video of the killer.

225
00:21:20,950 --> 00:21:24,090
If Professor Kang is searching for it,

226
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:30,000
it means he is the killer. Can't that be possible?

227
00:21:30,020 --> 00:21:32,070
It's your choice to believe that or not.

228
00:21:32,070 --> 00:21:38,110
Anyway, Professor Kang got leery from what Yun Yeong Gil said and was digging into Yun's past when he met Yi Yeong.

229
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:43,550
Perhaps she got something from Yun Yeong Gil?

230
00:21:43,550 --> 00:21:48,690
Yun Yeong Gil, who is dead now, said he left a gift for me.

231
00:21:48,690 --> 00:21:53,770
I don't know what it is.  Professor Kang suddenly appeared and I left.

232
00:22:15,510 --> 00:22:18,140
Yi Yeong, are you okay?

233
00:22:18,140 --> 00:22:22,090
Just now, Professor Kang came and left.

234
00:22:22,090 --> 00:22:26,430
He took the CD out of my bag. You must retrieve it.

235
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:29,970
I remember.  That was Ian's CD.

236
00:22:49,340 --> 00:22:51,650
What is this?

237
00:22:51,650 --> 00:22:54,830
An unlucky funeral march.

238
00:23:11,890 --> 00:23:14,370
What is this?  There's nothing here.

239
00:23:19,590 --> 00:23:22,130
That freaking leech.

240
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:58,040
Yi Yeong, are you all right?

241
00:23:58,040 --> 00:24:00,830
Calm down. Take deep breaths.

242
00:24:01,730 --> 00:24:04,340
Please call Dr. Park.

243
00:24:05,870 --> 00:24:08,060
Slowly.

244
00:24:08,060 --> 00:24:10,830
Slowly. Calm down.

245
00:24:27,990 --> 00:24:30,960
Why does your face look so bad?

246
00:24:31,930 --> 00:24:34,660
So many things are bothering me.

247
00:24:34,660 --> 00:24:38,310
After Prosecutor Lee called this morning, he said  we should meet immediately.

248
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:41,030
I think the prosecutor has something.

249
00:24:41,030 --> 00:24:43,870
They might soon make a move.

250
00:24:43,870 --> 00:24:47,920
Has he told you anything?

251
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:51,690
I'm lucky if I hear a single world in three days from him. What would he tell me?

252
00:24:51,690 --> 00:24:53,010
What will be the move?

253
00:24:53,010 --> 00:24:57,070
What would the prosecutor move be?  There's going to be an investigation.

254
00:24:57,070 --> 00:25:00,530
I think CEO Jang is pulling the strings.

255
00:25:00,530 --> 00:25:05,130
He's definitely putting a chokehold from every position.

256
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:12,480
This is related to the death of the man who killed Kim Ian in the hit-and-run case, isn't it?

257
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:17,910
Didn't Prosecutor Lee and you bury the hit-and-run case last year?

258
00:25:17,910 --> 00:25:20,400
What exactly have the two of you been doing?

259
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:25,310
Is this the time to argue about that? The prosecution is making a move.

260
00:25:25,310 --> 00:25:28,490
Have you forgotten that the school and the art foundation are one body?

261
00:25:28,490 --> 00:25:31,830
If I die, my sister-in-law will also die.

262
00:25:33,310 --> 00:25:38,820
Try to take action against Manager Yun. If you must, use this opportunity to take her out.

263
00:25:41,420 --> 00:25:43,230
What do you think?

264
00:25:43,230 --> 00:25:47,800
Do you think CEO Jang is really out to get us?

265
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:50,220
I also really don't know.

266
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:53,760
It's just that this time, the murder case stands out, bothering me.

267
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:56,330
I feel as if everything is tied to that incident.

268
00:25:56,330 --> 00:26:01,200
In any case, we should be prepared for an investigation by the prosecutor. I'll organize the ledgers that I have.

269
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:03,930
No, there's no need for that.

270
00:26:03,930 --> 00:26:10,880
Give all your ledgers regarding the foundation to me.

271
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:15,530
I will send Attorney Oh to you tomorrow. You should take some rest for the time being.

272
00:26:17,010 --> 00:26:20,310
Rest? What do you mean?

273
00:26:20,310 --> 00:26:26,400
To be honest, the responsibility for mismanaging the operation of funds for the foundation lies with with you, doesn't it?

274
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:29,340
You're the one who took the initiative on all this.

275
00:26:29,340 --> 00:26:32,020
I will compensate you for your efforts.

276
00:26:32,020 --> 00:26:35,780
I will give you my villa in Los Angeles.

277
00:26:36,890 --> 00:26:40,010
Why would you do that?

278
00:26:40,010 --> 00:26:44,720
Let's not make this complicated. Let's say something happens.

279
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:47,370
If this stops with you, you will get only one year in prison.

280
00:26:47,370 --> 00:26:51,730
But if this touches me or Professor Kang, things will become too big, and just think of the damage to our social image.

281
00:26:51,730 --> 00:26:56,180
Of course, once you finish your prison sentence, I will make sure to hire you again.

282
00:26:56,180 --> 00:26:59,770
President Go's position? It will be yours.

283
00:26:59,770 --> 00:27:02,190
Consider it carefully.

284
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:13,360
So, he just held rehearsal in that situation?

285
00:27:13,360 --> 00:27:17,920
Yes, we did, but I couldn't concentrate.

286
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:21,000
The Conductor wasn't in good condition, either.

287
00:27:22,420 --> 00:27:25,080
Someone has written a post calling him a murderer.

288
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:27,740
Would he be in the mood to conduct?

289
00:27:29,310 --> 00:27:34,590
Jenny, I'm sorry, but can you contact Yun for me?

290
00:27:34,590 --> 00:27:38,970
Yun? Didn't he come to visit?

291
00:27:38,970 --> 00:27:41,960
I saw him briefly a while ago,

292
00:27:44,020 --> 00:27:47,540
but I think Auntie and Unni aren't letting him see me.

293
00:27:48,330 --> 00:27:53,320
Unni has my cell phone, too, so I don't have a way to contact him.

294
00:27:54,150 --> 00:27:56,350
Please do that for me.

295
00:27:56,350 --> 00:27:58,010
Of course.

296
00:28:06,650 --> 00:28:08,120
I'll be back in an hour.

297
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:09,930
Thanks.

298
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:18,550
How are you feeling?

299
00:28:18,550 --> 00:28:22,090
It hurts, of course. My legs hurt,

300
00:28:22,090 --> 00:28:25,620
my head hurts, my arms, too.

301
00:28:36,220 --> 00:28:38,160
Are you alright?

302
00:28:39,450 --> 00:28:42,660
What about the CD that Professor Kang took?

303
00:28:46,030 --> 00:28:51,110
He threw it away. Looks like he smashed it and looked inside.

304
00:28:51,110 --> 00:28:55,110
In case something was hidden inside.

305
00:28:55,110 --> 00:28:58,420
Whether he removed anything, I don't know. That belonged to Ian?

306
00:28:58,420 --> 00:29:00,430
Yes.

307
00:29:00,430 --> 00:29:05,190
Due to the shock of this accident, I recovered some more memories from last year.

308
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:10,420
It was the song that was playing in Ian's car that day.

309
00:29:10,420 --> 00:29:14,320
Track 1

310
00:29:20,590 --> 00:29:27,250
After the accident, I think Yun Yeong Gil took that CD and was returning it to me.

311
00:29:27,250 --> 00:29:30,240
I don't know the reason.

312
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:36,570
As for that ballpoint pen, I was the one who gave it to Ian.

313
00:29:37,590 --> 00:29:41,840
After the performance with Asia Philharmonic Orchestra, in his dressing room.

314
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:44,330
Asia Philharmonic Orchestra & Kim Ian - Chopin Piano Concerto

315
00:29:44,330 --> 00:29:46,880
Kim Ian.

316
00:29:47,570 --> 00:29:49,520
One Year Ago

317
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:53,030
What? Where did he go?

318
00:29:57,120 --> 00:30:00,200
He didn't even hang this up.

319
00:30:14,220 --> 00:30:18,790
Sinyeong Music College
